:<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502220001: Config/Level/Mission/5022200/Act/Act502220001.json-->
:'''Lingsha:''' (Trailblazer), I'm so happy to see you~ Are you here at the Alchemy Commission today for me? What can I do for you?
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
:<!--Open NPC Menu-->
:{{DIcon}} I wanted to chat with you.
::'''Lingsha:''' Certainly. I don't have to consider or speculate unnecessarily when I'm talking with you. It's relaxing, like a head massage~
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502220002_15-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502220002_15-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Has work been going well lately?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220203-->
:::'''Lingsha:''' Ah... I don't know if I'd say that. Though the Alchemy Commission is small, there are complicated relations running between various different forces. It's like a miniature feudal state. It can be quite challenging to deal with.
:::'''Lingsha:''' Originally, I planned to make quick and decisive action and clear out these clique-forming pests as soon as possible. However, they have occupied key positions and I cannot currently find suitable personnel to take their places, so there is no way for me to simply get rid of them.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I love these kinds of stories of power struggles.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220206-->
::::'''Lingsha:''' If I may say so, I can't imagine that you enjoy this kind of "tepid stalemate." I imagine you're more excited by "the rise against the tyrant," "the fall of the mighty," or the "dramatic conflict?"
::::'''Lingsha:''' Is that correct? If it is, I am the same.
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502220211-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220211-->
::::'''Lingsha:''' But, when it comes to a wielding power, these Alchemy Commission knaves have no sway when it comes to the public eye. Though I may not be able to directly remove them, weakening their influence is a piece of cake.
::::'''Lingsha:''' Though they appear united in solidarity, they all have their own motives and desires. All I need to do is rouse mistrust between them and I can reduce them to nothing, breaking their group into myriads of tiny units.
::::'''Lingsha:''' When that time comes, they simply won't be strong enough to make any waves~
::::'''Lingsha:''' Of course, this is just stalling to gain time. Once I've managed to find suitable candidates to replace them, it will be time for their reckoning~ Hehe~
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I don't like these stories of deceit and subterfuge.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220209-->
::::'''Lingsha:''' Ah, if I had my way, there would be far less power struggles in this world. They are exhausting.
::::'''Lingsha:''' If that is not possible, I shall just have to face the exhaustion. As long as I'm satisfied with the result.
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502220211-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220211-->
