::{{DIcon|Talk}} Do you have any self-care recommendations?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220216-->
:::'''Lingsha:''' Umm... Ensure a stable balance of work and rest, make sure to eat properly and train regularly? This is really all the advice I can offer you. In other words, if you are in good health, this is the most logical suggestion.
:::'''Lingsha:''' Though it pains me to say it, though I am proficient in medicine, I still have a way to go to catch up with the elite healers.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Are you being modest, Master Lingsha?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220219-->
::::'''Lingsha:''' Ah, modesty will not decrease my workload. Fear not, I am not putting myself down.
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502220222-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220222-->
::::'''Lingsha:''' With miracle healers on the Xianzhou Luofu like the great Dragon Lady, my healing skills by comparison fall into the realm of things that the average person could come to comprehend. However, it's precisely for this reason that the queues at the Dragon Lady's clinic are ridiculous.
::::'''Lingsha:''' Healers differ greatly in terms of ability, experience, natural talent and area of expertise. Each healer has their own specialties, so it is necessary for someone to coordinate and organize healers based on their strengths and areas of practice...
::::'''Lingsha:''' That was why the Alliance made me the Luofu's Cauldron Master. Some have a duty to treat the illnesses of people, and some have a duty to cure the illnesses within the Alchemy Commission. So, do you see? The area of my healing expertise is slightly different.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
