::{{DIcon|Talk}} Master Lingsha, you smell lovely.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220226-->
:::'''Lingsha:''' ...You mean the smell of the incense?
:::'''Lingsha:''' I have always had a sense of smell that far surpasses others'. In addition to my experience of using, smelling, and learning about fragrances during my time with the Zhuming's Ardens Regia, I would say I know my stuff. Do you need some suggestions?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} How do you tell if an incense is good or bad?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220229-->
::::'''Lingsha:''' When it comes to incense, the first thing to do is open the box and take a whiff. If the smell comes rushing forth, it's probably had added fragrance and is a cheap product. High quality wooden incenses are subtle, with a natural and elegant aroma.
::::'''Lingsha:''' Another way to tell is to touch it. If there are too many wooden fibers, it can end up feeling rough. If it's too hard, that means that too much adhesive was added.
::::'''Lingsha:''' The most direct method to test it would just be to roast it, but not allow it to burn. Take a good smell when it is not properly lit, and you can get a clearer judgment of the scent's quality without the smoke interfering.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} How do you choose a suitable incense?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220233-->
::::'''Lingsha:''' I would recommend that you select according to your own preferences... If you're not too certain, you can think about the different situations where you might use it?
::::'''Lingsha:''' If you're in meditation or deep reflection, you can try a stronger and more potent fragrance. For example, I like incense like this when I'm reviewing various reports and materials.
::::'''Lingsha:''' If you're enjoying tea, reading, playing an instrument, or other similar activities, you might want something with a lighter, sweeter fragrance. I hear that the Express Navigator Himeko enjoys reading with a cup of coffee. I imagine this kind of incense would be more suitable for her.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502220236-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502220236-->
:::'''Lingsha:''' What do you think, some pretty good suggestions, right?
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: ALL_TALK_END-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: ALL_TALK_END-->
